# Role Access Assignment Guardrail

For every new feature, route, action, or UI control, assign access by role before implementation.

## Canonical roles
- `viewer`: read-only access; cannot create/update/delete.
- `staff`: operational updates (statuses, raw counts, routine supply updates).
- `admin`: full management (admin pages, add/edit/delete venues/items, user/account management).

## Required implementation pattern
1) Define permission mapping in the task (`viewer`, `staff`, `admin`) before coding.
2) Enforce access server-side first using route guards/decorators (`roles_required(...)`).
3) Mirror permissions in templates by hiding/disabling controls for unauthorized roles.
4) Never rely on UI visibility as security; unauthorized server actions must be blocked.

## Route/action defaults
- New read-only pages/endpoints: allow `viewer`, `staff`, `admin`.
- New mutating operational actions: allow `staff`, `admin`.
- New management/admin actions: allow `admin` only.

## Verification checklist (required)
- Unauthenticated users are redirected to login.
- `viewer` cannot trigger mutating actions.
- `staff` cannot access admin-only actions.
- `admin` can access all intended actions.
- Mobile and desktop UI show consistent role-based controls.

## Development safety
- Any dev-only bypass (for example quick-login buttons) must be gated to development mode and easy to remove.
